ZH: 这个儿童在家里经历了长时间的虐待。
EN: This child has experienced prolonged abuse at home.

ZH: 许多动物在实验室中遭受虐待。
EN: Many animals suffer from abuse in laboratories.

ZH: 她的前夫曾经虐待她，所以她离开了他。
EN: Her ex-husband used to abuse her, so she left him.

ZH: 我们必须采取行动来制止儿童虐待。
EN: We need to take action to stop child abuse.

ZH: 这家庭的儿童遭受了恶劣的虐待。
EN: The children in this family have suffered severe abuse.

ZH: 对动物进行虐待是不道德的行为。
EN: Abusing animals is unethical.

ZH: 她一直被她的父母虐待，直到她决定报警。
EN: She was abused by her parents until she decided to call the police.

ZH: 社会应该拒绝容忍家庭虐待的行为。
EN: Society should refuse to tolerate acts of domestic abuse.

ZH: 虐待行为会对受害者造成长期的心理创伤。
EN: Acts of abuse can cause long-lasting psychological trauma to the victims.

ZH: 心理虐待可能对一个人的自尊心造成重大伤害。
EN: Psychological abuse can cause significant damage to a person's self-esteem.

ZH: 他们对待那只狗非常残忍，完全是虐待行为。
EN: They treated that dog in a cruel manner, it was pure abuse.

ZH: 我们应该为遭受虐待的儿童提供支持和保护。
EN: We should provide support and protection for children who have suffered abuse.

ZH: 孩子们的福利机构致力于打击虐待和忽视行为。
EN: Child welfare organizations are dedicated to combating abuse and neglect.

ZH: 暴力和虐待是一种犯罪行为。
EN: Violence and abuse are criminal acts.

ZH: 她婆婆对她进行了长期的身体虐待。
EN: Her mother-in-law subjected her to prolonged physical abuse.

ZH: 他被指控虐待动物，并受到了指控。
EN: He was charged with animal abuse and faced charges.

ZH: 虐待行为不仅对受害者造成伤害，也对家庭产生负面影响。
EN: Abuse not only harms the victims but also has negative effects on the family.

ZH: 这个组织的使命是帮助虐待受害者重建他们的生活。
EN: The mission of this organization is to help abuse victims rebuild their lives.

ZH: 近年来，受虐待动物的报道有所增加，引起了公众的关注。
EN: In recent years, there has been an increase in reports of abused animals, arousing public attention.

ZH: 我们有责任报告任何家庭中发生的虐待行为。
EN: We have a responsibility to report any cases of abuse that happen in families.
